@@gMONK@@W

@@gHistory@@W
  The Monk tradition originated in the mountain monasteries that predated
  the great cities, where communities of ascetics developed physical
  disciplines as a form of living meditation. They discovered that breath
  control, posture, and movement could be refined to a point where the body
  itself became the instrument of something beyond ordinary physical
  capacity. The first combat-capable Monks were not warriors -- they were
  scholars of the physical form who found, sometimes reluctantly, that their
  disciplines translated into devastating martial efficiency. They codified
  their methods in what came to be called the Interior Forms, a system that
  treated every strike not as aggression but as applied understanding.
  Pugilists who return to study the Interior Forms find the forms have been
  waiting for them all along.

Monks are disciplined impact-fighters who convert breath control and posture
mastery into relentless unarmed pressure.

